{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778467380262,"sessionID":"ses_1eb261946ffeivpfqyEeGx6tvF","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-984d598f55d953d3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/src/ontology/Makefile"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/src/ontology/Makefile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: all: stage_release\n2: \n3: SHELL=./stamp.sh\n4: \n5: # ----------------------------------------\n6: # CORE VARIABLES\n7: # ----------------------------------------\n8: \n9: # base URI for all OBO library ontologies\n10: OBO=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo\n11: \n12: # OBO name of this ontology (always lowercase)\n13: ONT=go\n14: \n15: # Base URL for ontology\n16: BASE=$(OBO)/$(ONT)\n17: \n18: # Source file edited by editors\n19: SRC=$(ONT)-edit.obo\n20: \n21: # Staging release directory\n22: RELEASEDIR=../../target\n23: RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS=$(RELEASEDIR)/imports\n24: \n25: # ROBOT is the main release release tool\n26: ROBOT_ENV = ROBOT_JAVA_ARGS=-Xmx12G\n27: ROBOT = $(ROBOT_ENV) robot --catalog catalog-v001.xml\n28: \n29: # OWLTools is a swiss-army knife;\n30: # It does some things robot can't do, but eventually functionality should\n31: # move to robot\n32: OWLTOOLS_ENV = OWLTOOLS_MEMORY=6G\n33: OWLTOOLS = $(OWLTOOLS_ENV) owltools\n34: \n35: #DOSDP is used for turning tsv files into pieces of ontologies for imports\n36: DOSDP_ENV = JAVA_OPTS=-Xmx6G\n37: DOSDP_TOOLS = $(DOSDP_ENV) dosdp-tools\n38: \n39: AMM_ENV = JAVA_OPTS=-Xmx6G\n40: AMM = $(AMM_ENV) amm --silent\n41: \n42: # OWL catalogs map ontology IRIs to local paths\n43: USECAT= --use-catalog\n44: \n45: # obo-centric checks and and filters\n46: PERLCHECK= ../util/check-obo-for-standard-release.pl\n47: PERLFILTER= ../util/filter-obo-for-standard-release.pl\n48: \n49: # Release IRIs are of the form\n50: #  obo/go/releases/YYYY-MM-DD/$FILE\n51: #\n52: # To make snapshot releases:\n53: #\n54: #   $ RELEASE_SUFFIX=SNAPSHOT make prepare_release\n55: #\n56: RELEASEDATE ?= `date +%Y-%m-%d`\n57: RELEASE_SUFFIX=\n58: RELEASE_URIBASE = $(BASE)/releases/$(RELEASEDATE)$(RELEASE_SUFFIX)\n59: \n60: # basic relations are part_of & 3 regulations relations\n61: GO_BASIC_RELATIONS = BFO:0000050 RO:0002211 RO:0002212 RO:0002213\n62: \n63: # extend with has_part, occurs_in and during relations\n64: # - this is the set used in the main go file\n65: GO_MAIN_RELATIONS = $(GO_BASIC_RELATIONS) BFO:0000051 BFO:0000066 RO:0002091 RO:0002092 RO:0002093\n66: \n67: GO_PLUS = extensions/go-plus\n68: GO_GAF = extensions/go-gaf\n69: GO_AMIGO = extensions/go-amigo\n70: GO_LEGO = extensions/go-lego\n71: GO_LEGO_REACTO = extensions/go-lego-reacto\n72: \n73: SPARQLDIR = ../sparql\n74: REPORTDIR = $(RELEASEDIR)/reports\n75: \n76: # ----------------------------------------\n77: # TOP LEVEL TARGETS\n78: # ----------------------------------------\n79: \n80: stage_release: imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl test $(ONT).owl $(ONT).obo $(ONT).json.gz $(GO_PLUS).owl $(GO_PLUS).json.gz go-base.owl $(GO_GAF).owl $(GO_AMIGO).owl $(GO_LEGO).owl $(GO_LEGO_REACTO).owl go-basic.obo go-basic.json.gz extensions/rhea-reactions.ttl imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.obo subset-owls subset-reports generate-mappings\n81: \n82: test: datalog-violations.tsv $(SRC)-check basic-cycles.tsv sparql_test check_all_taxon_constraints_columns change-report.txt reasoned.ofn unsatisfiable present_in_taxon_check.ofn chebi_pH_7_3_check\n83: \n84: travis_test: check_all_taxon_constraints_columns datalog-violations.tsv chebi_pH_7_3_check $(SRC)-check travis_build change-report.txt\n85: \n86: # This target combines features from reasoned.ofn, enhanced.ofn, sparql_test into a faster mode for Travis/GitHub Actions.\n87: # These must be kept in sync.\n88: # The convert step is here only to work around https://github.com/ontodev/robot/issues/1250\n89: travis_build: go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn\n90: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn -o travis_build_dummy_out.ofn verify --queries $(VARGS) -O reports/ merge --collapse-import-closure false -i imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl -i imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl -i ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn -i imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl remove --term 'IAO:0000116' --axioms annotation --signature true query --update ../sparql/add-skos-xrefs.ru --update ../sparql/remove-broad-xrefs.ru --update ../sparql/remove-related-xrefs.ru remove --select 'complement' --drop-axiom-annotations 'oboInOwl:source' reason -r ELK -e asserted-only --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural relax reduce annotate -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$(ONT).owl --annotation owl:versionInfo $(RELEASEDATE) convert --add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld -o travis_build_dummy_out.ofn verify --queries $(SPARQLDIR)/multiple-class-links-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/obsolete-reference-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/missing_superclass-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/different-namespace-violation.sparql -O reports/\n91: \n92: unsatisfiable: $(GO_GAF).owl\n93: \t$(ROBOT) reason --reasoner ELK --input extensions/go-gaf.owl -D $(RELEASEDIR)/core_dump.owl || true\n94: \n95: full_test: test $(ONT).obo\n96: \n97: # note that most derived files are kept separate from source files, in $(RELEASEDIR)\n98: clean: clean_target clean_imports\n99: clean_target:\n100: \trm -rf $(RELEASEDIR)/*\n101: \n102: # copies from staged area to target\n103: prepare_release:\n104: \techo \"Base Version IRI: $(RELEASE_URIBASE)\"\n105: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/extensions &&\\\n106: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/subsets &&\\\n107: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/reports &&\\\n108: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/external2go &&\\\n109: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS) &&\\\n110: \tcp $(ONT).owl $(ONT).obo $(ONT).json $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n111: \tcp imports/*.owl $(RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS) &&\\\n112: \tcp imports/*.obo $(RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS) &&\\\n113: \tcp extensions/* $(RELEASEDIR)/extensions &&\\\n114: \tcp external2go/* $(RELEASEDIR)/external2go &&\\\n115: \tcp go-basic.* $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n116: \tcp go-base.owl $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n117: \tfind subsets/ -maxdepth 1 -type f ! -name '*.tmp' -exec cp {} $(RELEASEDIR)/subsets/ \\; &&\\\n118: \tcp reports/* $(RELEASEDIR)/reports &&\\\n119: \techo \"Release files are now in $(RELEASEDIR)\"\n120: \n121: # deploy to S3\n122: # URLs will be of the form https://s3.amazonaws.com/go-data-product-current/ontology/subsets/go-basic.json.gz\n123: S3CFG = ~/.s3cfg.go-pipeline-push-agent\n124: # https://build.berkeleybop.org/job/release-go-ontology-daily-snapshot/\n125: deploy-snapshot:\n126: \tcd $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n127: \ts3cmd -c $(S3CFG) --acl-public --mime-type=application/rdf+xml sync ./  s3://go-data-product-snapshot/ontology/\n128: \n129: deploy-release:\n130: \tcd $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n131: \ts3cmd -c $(S3CFG) --acl-public --mime-type=application/rdf+xml sync ./  s3://go-data-product-current/ontology/\n132: \ts3cmd -c $(S3CFG) --acl-public --mime-type=application/rdf+xml sync ./  s3://go-data-product-release/$(RELEASEDATE)/ontology/\n133: \n134: \n135: # ----------------------------------------\n136: # GENERIC TRANSFORMS\n137: # ----------------------------------------\n138: \n139: %.gz: %\n140: \tgzip -c $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n141: \n142: %.json: %.ofn\n143: \t$(ROBOT) convert --input $< -f json -o $@\n144: .PRECIOUS: %.json\n145: \n146: # ----------------------------------------\n147: # CHECKS AND BALANCES\n148: # ----------------------------------------\n149: \n150: # TODO: use json form of this file\n151: # See also: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/13837\n152: # See also: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18870\n153: GO.xrf_abbs: $(SRC)\n154: \twget http://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/db-xrefs.legacy -O $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@ && touch $@\n155: \n156: $(SRC)-check: $(SRC) GO.xrf_abbs\n157: \t$(PERLCHECK) --disable-isa-incomplete --disable-whitespace-check --xref-abbs GO.xrf_abbs $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n158: \n159: # consider using snapshot release\n160: PREVIOUS=go-lastrelease.owl\n161: PREVIOUS_OBO=go-lastrelease.obo\n162: PREVIOUS_PLUS=go-plus-lastrelease.owl\n163: $(PREVIOUS): $(SRC)\n164: \twget $(OBO)/go.owl -O $@ && touch $@\n165: \n166: $(PREVIOUS_OBO): $(SRC)\n167: \twget $(OBO)/go.obo -O $@ && touch $@\n168: \n169: $(PREVIOUS_PLUS): $(SRC)\n170: \twget $(OBO)/go/extensions/go-plus.owl -O $@ && touch $@\n171: \n172: # ensure no IDs are lost\n173: change-report.txt: $(SRC) $(PREVIOUS)\n174: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $(USECAT) $< --verify-changes -p $(PREVIOUS) -o $@ --id-prefix-filter GO: --check-missing-labels && touch $@\n175: \n176: go-owl-diff.md: $(PREVIOUS) go.ofn\n177: \t$(ROBOT) diff --left $(PREVIOUS) --right go.ofn --format markdown -o $@\n178: \n179: go-plus-owl-diff.md: $(PREVIOUS_PLUS) $(GO_PLUS).ofn\n180: \t$(ROBOT) diff --left $(PREVIOUS_PLUS) --right $(GO_PLUS).ofn --format markdown -o $@\n181: \n182: go-obo-txt-diff.md: $(PREVIOUS_OBO) go.obo\n183: \t{ echo \"# Textual diff for go.obo\\\\n\"; echo \"\\`\\`\\`diff\"; diff -u $(PREVIOUS_OBO) go.obo; echo \"\\`\\`\\`\"; } >$@\n184: \n185: go-obo-status.md: $(PREVIOUS_OBO) go.obo ../gh_pages_templates/go-obo-status.md\n186: \t{ echo \"---\"; runoak -i simpleobo:go.obo statistics --group-by-obo-namespace --compare-with simpleobo:$(PREVIOUS_OBO); echo \"---\"; cat ../gh_pages_templates/go-obo-status.md; } >$@\n187: \n188: # ----------------------------------------\n189: # OWL\n190: # ----------------------------------------\n191: \n192: #Uses file provided by Reactome to generate xrefs for import\n193: \n194: ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt:\n195: \twget -O $@ --no-check-certificate https://reactome.org/download/current/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt\n196: \n197: ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt:\n198: \twget -O $@ --no-check-certificate https://reactome.org/download/current/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n199: \n200: imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl: ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n201: \tmkdir -p reactome-tmp\n202: \tsed -i '1s/.*/Identifier\\tName\\tdefined_class/' ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt\n203: \tsed -i '1d' ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n204: \tperl -i.bak -pe 's/[^[:ascii:]]//g' ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt\n205: \tperl -i.bak -pe 's/[^[:ascii:]]//g' ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n206: \tcat ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt >reactome-tmp/combined.txt\n207: \trm ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt.bak\n208: \trm ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt.bak\n209: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --template=xref_dosdp_yaml/reactome_xref.yaml --infile=reactome-tmp/combined.txt --outfile=reactome-tmp/reactome_xrefs.ofn --obo-prefixes=true\n210: \t$(ROBOT) convert --input reactome-tmp/reactome_xrefs.ofn --output imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl annotate --ontology-iri $(BASE)/imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n211: \n212: # Remove reactome_xrefs_import.owl and go_taxon_constraints.owl from imports. These are merged in directly in enhanced.ofn\n213: go-edit-trimmed-imports.obo: $(SRC)\n214: \tgrep -v '^import: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go/imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl' $< |\\\n215: \tgrep -v '^import: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go/imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl' >$@\n216: \n217: go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn: go-edit-trimmed-imports.obo ../util/filter-rhea-xrefs.sc ../resources/rhea.rdf\n218: \t$(AMM) ../util/filter-rhea-xrefs.sc $< catalog-v001.xml ../resources/rhea.rdf $@\n219: \n220: # merge in some imported GO modules\n221: # remove editor-only annotations\n222: # convert some xrefs to skos properties - only for prefixes defined in the SPARQL update file\n223: # NOTE - the beginning 'annotate' command is used only to work around this ROBOT bug when merge is the first command: \n224: # https://github.com/ontodev/robot/issues/1250\n225: # NOTE - 'convert --add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld' is necessary until ROBOT issue https://github.com/ontodev/robot/issues/1266 is fixed\n226: enhanced.ofn: go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn ../sparql/add-skos-xrefs.ru ../sparql/remove-broad-xrefs.ru ../sparql/remove-related-xrefs.ru\n227: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn --annotation owl:versionInfo $(RELEASEDATE) merge --collapse-import-closure false -i imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl -i imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl -i imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl remove --term 'IAO:0000116' --axioms annotation --signature true query --update ../sparql/add-skos-xrefs.ru --update ../sparql/remove-broad-xrefs.ru --update ../sparql/remove-related-xrefs.ru remove --select 'complement' --drop-axiom-annotations 'oboInOwl:source' annotate --annotation owl:versionInfo $(RELEASEDATE) convert --add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld -o $@\n228: \n229: # reasoned.ofn is equivalent to editors source, after materialize-reason-relax-reduce pipeline\n230: # note: we keep this as a distinct intermediate target as the ontology IRI needs to be 'go' for Oort to work...\n231: reasoned.ofn: enhanced.ofn $(SRC)-check\n232: \t$(ROBOT) materialize -i $< -r ELK --term BFO:0000050 reason -r ELK -e asserted-only --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural relax reduce annotate -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$(ONT).owl -o $@\n233: \n234: present_in_taxon_check.ofn: enhanced.ofn ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn\n235: \t$(ROBOT) merge --collapse-import-closure false -i $< -i ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn reason -r ELK -e asserted-only --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural -o $@\n236: \n237: # equivalent to reasoned, but we rename\n238: # TODO cleanup redundancies with merge here and with go-base\n239: # note: do not run 'reason' after go-computed-taxon-constraints.owl is merged; some desired logical redundancy may be lost\n240: $(GO_PLUS).ofn: reasoned.ofn imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.owl\n241: \t$(ROBOT) unmerge -i $< -i imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl merge --collapse-import-closure true --include-annotations false merge -i imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.owl annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n242: \n243: $(GO_PLUS).owl: $(GO_PLUS).ofn\n244: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n245: .PRECIOUS: $(GO_PLUS).owl\n246: \n247: # Create release file containing GO-asserted axioms, no external axioms.\n248: # GO artifacts to merge are hardcoded here.\n249: go-base.owl: $(GO_PLUS).ofn\n250: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --select imports --trim false remove --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_' --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GOREL_' --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GOCHE_' --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_Union_' --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false merge -i extensions/go-gci.owl -i extensions/go-bridge.owl -i extensions/ro_pending.owl -i imports/x-disjoint.ofn annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n251: \n252: $(GO_GAF).owl: extensions/go-gaf-edit.ofn $(GO_PLUS).owl extensions/gorel.owl mirror/cl.owl mirror/taxslim.owl mirror/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl\n253: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< --collapse-import-closure true --include-annotations false reason -r ELK --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --remove-redundant-subclass-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n254: \n255: $(GO_AMIGO).owl: extensions/go-amigo-edit.ofn $(GO_GAF).owl extensions/go-modules-annotations.owl extensions/go-taxon-subsets.owl mirror/eco.owl mirror/pato.owl mirror/po.owl mirror/chebi.owl mirror/uberon.owl mirror/wbbt.owl\n256: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< --collapse-import-closure true --include-annotations false reason -r ELK --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --remove-redundant-subclass-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n257: \n258: # Not all imports are being pre-mirrored; the ones that are should be dependencies\n259: $(GO_LEGO).owl: extensions/go-lego-edit.ofn $(GO_PLUS).owl mirror/ro.owl extensions/legorel.owl extensions/go-bfo-bridge.owl mirror/taxslim.owl mirror/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl mirror/cl.owl mirror/uberon.owl mirror/users.ttl mirror/groups.ttl imports/go-lego-chebi-import.owl mirror/wbbt.owl mirror/eco.owl\n260: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< --collapse-import-closure true --include-annotations false reason -r ELK --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --remove-redundant-subclass-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural relax reduce --named-classes-only true annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n261: \n262: extensions/reacto.owl: $(GO_LEGO).owl mirror/chebi.owl\n263: \tmkdir -p reacto-tmp\n264: \twget -O ./reacto-tmp/biopax2go.jar --no-check-certificate https://github.com/geneontology/pathways2GO/releases/download/v1.1.4/biopax2go.jar\n265: \twget -O ./reacto-tmp/biopax.zip --no-check-certificate https://reactome.org/download/current/biopax.zip\n266: \tunzip -o ./reacto-tmp/biopax.zip -d ./reacto-tmp/\n267: \tjava -jar -Xmx8G ./reacto-tmp/biopax2go.jar -b ./reacto-tmp/Homo_sapiens.owl -reacto ./extensions/reacto -lego $(GO_LEGO).owl -chebi ./mirror/chebi.owl\n268: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i extensions/reacto.ttl -o extensions/reacto.owl\n269: \trm ./reacto-tmp/*\n270: \trmdir ./reacto-tmp\n271: \n272: $(GO_LEGO_REACTO).owl: extensions/go-lego-reacto-edit.ofn $(GO_LEGO).owl extensions/reacto.owl\n273: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< --collapse-import-closure true --include-annotations false reason -r ELK --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --remove-redundant-subclass-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural relax reduce --named-classes-only true annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n274: \n275: # ----------------------------------------\n276: # OBO and subsets\n277: # ----------------------------------------\n278: \n279: # while go-plus is the full version, the successive releases eliminate various things to simplify the\n280: # file, including\n281: #  - no imports or external ontologies\n282: #  - smaller set of relations (v small for go-basic)\n283: #  - ...\n284: # go.obo is a simplified; we use oort to remove imports etc\n285: $(ONT)-pre.ofn: reasoned.ofn\n286: \t$(ROBOT) materialize --input $< --reasoner ELK $(addprefix --term ,$(GO_MAIN_RELATIONS)) remove --select imports --trim true remove --select '<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_*>' --select complement --select classes --signature true --trim true remove $(addprefix --term ,$(GO_MAIN_RELATIONS)) --select complement --select object-properties --signature true --trim true annotate -O $(OBO)/$(ONT).owl -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$(ONT).owl convert -f owl --output $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n287: \n288: $(ONT)-pre-reduced.ofn: $(ONT)-pre.ofn\n289: \t$(ROBOT) reduce -r elk -i $< -o $@\n290: .PRECIOUS: $(ONT)-pre-reduced.ofn\n291: \n292: go.ofn: $(ONT)-pre-reduced.ofn\n293: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --select 'complement' --drop-axiom-annotations 'IAO:0000233' -o $@\n294: \n295: go.owl: go.ofn\n296: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n297: \n298: go.obo: $(ONT).ofn\n299: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@.tmp.obo &&\\\n300: \tcp $@.tmp.obo $@\n301: #\t$(PERLCHECK) --disable-xrf-abbs-check --disable-multiply-labeled-edge --disable-whitespace-check $@.tmp.obo\n302: \n303: # remove non-basic relationship types (e.g. has_part)\n304: # assuming materialization step already done for these properties when making go.obo\n305: # NOTE - '--add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld' is necessary due to https://github.com/ontodev/robot/issues/1266\n306: go-simple-filtered.ofn: go.ofn $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-cross-namespace-relations.ru $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-mf-regulates-links.ru $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-multiply-labeled-edges.ru\n307: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< $(addprefix --term ,$(GO_BASIC_RELATIONS)) --select complement --select object-properties --signature true --trim true remove --term 'oboInOwl:created_by' --term 'oboInOwl:creation_date' --term 'IAO:0000233' --term 'IAO:0000589' --term 'RO:0002175' --signature true --trim true remove --axioms \"DisjointClasses EquivalentClasses\" query --update $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-cross-namespace-relations.ru --update $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-mf-regulates-links.ru --update $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-multiply-labeled-edges.ru convert --add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld -f ofn --output $@\n308: \n309: go-basic.ofn: go-simple-filtered.ofn\n310: \t$(ROBOT) reduce -r elk -i $< -o $@\n311: \n312: go-basic.owl: go-basic.ofn\n313: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n314: #FIXME rewrite perl filter/check\n315: #\t$(PERLFILTER) $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@ && $(PERLCHECK) --disable-xrf-abbs-check --disable-whitespace-check $@\n316: \n317: go-basic.obo: go-basic.ofn\n318: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n319: \n320: # check for cycles in go-basic\n321: basic.facts: go-basic.owl\n322: \triot -q --output=ntriples $< | sed 's/ /\\t/' | sed 's/ /\\t/' | sed 's/ \\.$$//' >$@\n323: \n324: basic-cycles.tsv: basic.facts ../util/cycles.dl\n325: \tsouffle ../util/cycles.dl && mv cycle.csv $@ &&\\\n326: \t( [ -s $@ ] && { cat $@; exit 1; } || true ) # exit with an error if the output is not empty\n327: \n328: # ----------------------------------------\n329: # SUBSETS AND REPORTS\n330: # ----------------------------------------\n331: # Currently the only per-subset report is id-label pairs\n332: # See: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/14028\n333: \n334: PUBLISH_SUBSETS = gocheck_do_not_annotate gocheck_obsoletion_candidate goslim_agr goslim_candida goslim_chembl goslim_drosophila goslim_euk_cellular_processes_ribbon goslim_flybase_ribbon goslim_generic goslim_metagenomics goslim_mouse goslim_pir goslim_plant goslim_plant_ribbon goslim_pombe goslim_prokaryote_ribbon goslim_synapse goslim_yeast goslim_prokaryote goslim_virus\n335: \n336: SUBSET_OWLS = $(patsubst %,subsets/%.owl,$(PUBLISH_SUBSETS))\n337: subset-owls: $(SUBSET_OWLS)\n338: \n339: # Also generates %.obo and %.json\n340: subsets/subset-terms.tsv: $(ONT).owl $(SPARQLDIR)/subset-terms.sparql\n341: \t$(ROBOT) query -i $< -f tsv --query $(word 2,$^) $@\n342: \n343: subsets/subset-properties.tsv: $(ONT).owl $(SPARQLDIR)/subset-properties.sparql\n344: \t$(ROBOT) query -i $< -f tsv --query $(word 2,$^) $@.tmp && sed 's/\"//g' $@.tmp >$@ && rm -f $@.tmp\n345: \n346: subsets/%-terms.txt: subsets/subset-terms.tsv subsets/subset-properties.tsv\n347: \tgrep '\"$*\"' $< | cut -f1 | sed 's/\"//g' >$@.tmp && cat $@.tmp $(word 2,$^) >$@ && rm -f $@.tmp\n348: \n349: # Also generates %.obo and %.json\n350: subsets/%.owl: $(ONT).ofn subsets/%-terms.txt\n351: \t$(ROBOT) extract --method subset -i $< --term-file $(word 2,$^) annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ --annotation owl:versionInfo $(RELEASEDATE) -o $@ convert -o $(patsubst %.owl,%.obo,$@) convert -o $(patsubst %.owl,%.json,$@)\n352: \n353: # so far we only make simple .tsv reports\n354: SUBSET_REPORTS = $(patsubst %,%.tsv,$(basename $(SUBSET_OWLS)))\n355: subset-reports: $(SUBSET_REPORTS)\n356: subsets/%.tsv: subsets/%.owl\n357: \t$(ROBOT) query -f tsv -i $< -s ../sparql/labels.sparql $@\n358: \n359: # ----------------------------------------\n360: # IMPORT MODULES\n361: # ----------------------------------------\n362: \n363: IMPORTS = chebi cl po pato ro ncbitaxon uberon ddanat fao oba so opl reactome_xrefs go_taxon_constraints\n364: IMPORTS_OWL = $(patsubst %, imports/%_import.owl,$(IMPORTS)) $(patsubst %, imports/%_import.obo,$(IMPORTS))\n365: \n366: # Make this target to regenerate ALL\n367: all_imports: $(IMPORTS_OWL)\n368: clean_imports:\n369: \trm mirror/*\n370: \n371: seed.txt: enhanced.ofn imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl imports/go-taxon-groupings-edit.owl ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl\n372: \t$(ROBOT) merge --collapse-import-closure false -i enhanced.ofn -i imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl -i imports/go-taxon-groupings-edit.owl -i ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn -i imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl query -f csv --select ../sparql/terms.sparql $@\n373: \n374: # Specialize seed terms for PR. The inclusion of taxon IRIs in the full seed was causing PR to pull\n375: # in overly specific proteins (e.g. human forms of everything) and referencing gene IRIs. This is kind\n376: # of a general problem to balance for all import module extractions; need to come up with a consistent approach.\n377: imports/pr_terms_combined.txt: imports/pr_terms.txt seed.txt\n378: \tcat $^ | grep 'PR_' > $@\n379: \n380: # Specialize seed terms for OPL.\n381: imports/opl_terms_combined.txt: imports/opl_terms.txt seed.txt\n382: \tcat $^ | grep 'OPL_' > $@\n383: \n384: imports/%_terms_combined.txt: imports/%_terms.txt seed.txt\n385: \tcat $^ > $@\n386: \n387: # Use ROBOT for imports\n388: \n389: imports/%_import_pre.owl: mirror/%.owl imports/%_terms_combined.txt $(SRC)\n390: \t$(ROBOT) extract -i $< -T imports/$*_terms_combined.txt --method BOT reason --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural annotate -O $(BASE)/imports/$*_import.owl -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/imports/$*_import.owl -o $@\n391: .PRECIOUS: imports/%_import_pre.owl\n392: \n393: imports/ncbitaxon_import.owl: imports/ncbitaxon_import_pre.owl ../sparql/add-taxon-sibling-disjoints.ru ../sparql/add-taxon-disjoints.ru ../sparql/add-in-taxon-disjoints.ru\n394: \t$(ROBOT) query -i $< --update ../sparql/add-taxon-sibling-disjoints.ru --update ../sparql/add-taxon-disjoints.ru --update ../sparql/add-in-taxon-disjoints.ru -o $@\n395: \n396: # Ensure every row in the taxon constraints files has the same number of columns (only one line should be output by `sort`)\n397: check_taxon_constraint_columns_%: ../taxon_constraints/%.tsv\n398: \tawk -F'\\t' '{print NF}' $< | sort -nu | wc -l | sed -e 's/[[:blank:]]//g' | grep -q \"^1$$\" && exit 0 || (echo \"ERROR: wrong number of columns in $<. Check for spaces where tabs should be.\" && exit 1)\n399: \n400: check_all_taxon_constraints_columns: check_taxon_constraint_columns_only_in_taxon check_taxon_constraint_columns_never_in_taxon check_taxon_constraint_columns_present_in_taxon\n401: \n402: .PHONY: check_all_taxon_constraints_columns\n403: \n404: ../taxon_constraints/only_in_taxon.ofn: ../taxon_constraints/only_in_taxon.yaml ../taxon_constraints/only_in_taxon.tsv\n405: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --infile=../taxon_constraints/only_in_taxon.tsv --obo-prefixes=true --template=$< --outfile=$@\n406: \n407: ../taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.ofn: ../taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.yaml ../taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.tsv\n408: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --infile=../taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.tsv --obo-prefixes=true --template=$< --outfile=$@\n409: \n410: ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn: ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.yaml ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.tsv\n411: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --infile=../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.tsv --generate-defined-class=true --obo-prefixes=true --template=$< --outfile=$@\n412: \n413: ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.ofn: ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.yaml ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.tsv\n414: \techo 'defined_class\tdefined_class_label\ttaxon\ttaxon_label\tsource' >../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.tsv &&\\\n415: \ttail -n +2 ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.tsv >>../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.tsv &&\\\n416: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --infile=../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.tsv --obo-prefixes=true --template=$< --outfile=$@\n417: \n418: imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl: ../taxon_constraints/only_in_taxon.ofn ../taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.ofn ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.ofn\n419: \t$(ROBOT) merge $(addprefix -i , $^) annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -o $@\n420: \n421: imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.owl: $(SRC) $(SPARQLDIR)/taxon-constraints-materialization.ru ../util/materialize-taxon-constraints.dl\n422: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< query --update $(SPARQLDIR)/taxon-constraints-materialization.ru -o taxon-constraints-materialization-temp.ofn &&\\\n423: \tJAVA_OPTS=-Xmx12G relation-graph --ontology-file taxon-constraints-materialization-temp.ofn --output-file taxon-constraints-materialization-temp.nt --property 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162' --output-subclasses true --reflexive-subclasses false &&\\\n424: \tsed 's/ /\\t/' taxon-constraints-materialization-temp.nt | sed 's/ /\\t/' | sed 's/ \\.$$//' >taxonconstraintsrelationgraph.facts &&\\\n425: \tsouffle ../util/materialize-taxon-constraints.dl &&\\\n426: \tsed -E 's|<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/([^[:space:]]+)_([[:digit:]]+)>|\\1:\\2|g' computed_only_in_taxon.csv | sed '1s/^/defined_class\\ttaxon\\n/' >computed_only_in_taxon.tsv &&\\\n427: \tsed -E 's|<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/([^[:space:]]+)_([[:digit:]]+)>|\\1:\\2|g' computed_never_in_taxon.csv | sed '1s/^/defined_class\\ttaxon\\n/' >computed_never_in_taxon.tsv &&\\\n428: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --obo-prefixes=true --template=../taxon_constraints/computed_only_in_taxon.yaml --infile=computed_only_in_taxon.tsv --outfile=computed_only_in_taxon.tmp.ofn &&\\\n429: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --obo-prefixes=true --template=../taxon_constraints/computed_never_in_taxon.yaml --infile=computed_never_in_taxon.tsv --outfile=computed_never_in_taxon.tmp.ofn &&\\\n430: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i computed_only_in_taxon.tmp.ofn -O $(BASE)/$@ merge -i computed_never_in_taxon.tmp.ofn -o $@\n431: \n432: imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.obo: imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.owl\n433: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.tmp.obo && grep -v '^owl-axioms' imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.tmp.obo >$@\n434: \n435: imports/%_import.owl: imports/%_import_pre.owl\n436: \tcp $< $@\n437: \n438: imports/chebi_import.owl: bio-chebi.owl imports/chebi_terms_combined.txt $(SRC)\n439: \t$(ROBOT) extract -i bio-chebi.owl -T imports/chebi_terms_combined.txt --method BOT remove --term 'http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label' --term 'http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset' --term 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go#chebi_ph7_3' --select complement --select annotation-properties --signature true annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n440: .PRECIOUS: imports/chebi_import.owl\n441: \n442: imports/%_import.obo: imports/%_import.owl\n443: \t$(ROBOT) convert --input $< --format obo --check false --output $@.tmp && grep -v ^owl-axioms: $@.tmp > $@\n444: \n445: # ----------------------------------------\n446: # CACHEING EXTERNAL ONTOLOGIES\n447: # ----------------------------------------\n448: \n449: # Fix external ontologies to specific release versions if necessary. These should be updated regularly! Otherwise use the standard PURL.\n450: CHEBI_SOURCE=http://ftp.ebi.ac.uk/pub/databases/chebi/archive/rel247/ontology/chebi.owl.gz # ChEBI is currently missing a version IRI\n451: CL_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/cl/releases/2025-01-08/cl-base.owl\n452: FAO_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fao/fao-base.owl\n453: PATO_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/pato/pato-base.owl\n454: UBERON_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/uberon-base.owl\n455: WBBT_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/wbbt/wbbt-base.owl\n456: ECO_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/eco/eco-basic.owl\n457: OBA_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/oba/subsets/oba-basic.obo\n458: COB_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/cob.owl\n459: \n460: WGET_OUT = -O $@.tmp && cp $@.tmp $@ && touch $@\n461: \n462: mirror:\n463: \tmkdir $@\n464: \n465: # special case: download obo for speed for ncbitaxon.\n466: # note also that here we only trigger new downloads if ncbitaxon_terms.txt is touched\n467: mirror/ncbitaxon-download.owl: imports/ncbitaxon_terms.txt\n468: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/ncbitaxon.obo $(WGET_OUT)\n469: .PRECIOUS: mirror/ncbitaxon-download.owl\n470: \n471: mirror/taxslim.owl: $(SRC)\n472: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/ncbitaxon/subsets/taxslim.owl $(WGET_OUT)\n473: .PRECIOUS: mirror/taxslim.owl\n474: \n475: mirror/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl: $(SRC)\n476: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/ncbitaxon/subsets/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl $(WGET_OUT)\n477: .PRECIOUS: mirror/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl\n478: \n479: mirror/pr-download.owl: $(SRC)\n480: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/pr.owl $(WGET_OUT)\n481: .PRECIOUS: mirror/pr-download.owl\n482: \n483: # special case: download gz for speed for chebi\n484: mirror/chebi-download.owl: $(SRC)\n485: \twget --no-check-certificate $(CHEBI_SOURCE) -O $@.tmp.gz && mv $@.tmp.gz $@.gz && gunzip -f $@.gz && touch $@\n486: .PRECIOUS: mirror/chebi-download.owl\n487: \n488: mirror/uberon-download.owl: $(SRC)\n489: \twget --no-check-certificate $(UBERON_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n490: .PRECIOUS: mirror/uberon-download.owl\n491: \n492: mirror/oba-download.owl: $(SRC)\n493: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBA_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n494: .PRECIOUS: mirror/oba-download.owl\n495: \n496: mirror/cl-download.owl: $(SRC)\n497: \twget --no-check-certificate $(CL_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n498: .PRECIOUS: mirror/cl-download.owl\n499: \n500: mirror/fao-download.owl: $(SRC)\n501: \twget --no-check-certificate $(FAO_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n502: .PRECIOUS: mirror/fao-download.owl\n503: \n504: mirror/pato-download.owl: $(SRC)\n505: \twget --no-check-certificate $(PATO_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n506: .PRECIOUS: mirror/pato-download.owl\n507: \n508: mirror/wbbt-download.owl: $(SRC)\n509: \twget --no-check-certificate $(WBBT_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n510: .PRECIOUS: mirror/wbbt-download.owl\n511: \n512: mirror/eco-download.owl: $(SRC)\n513: \twget --no-check-certificate $(ECO_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n514: .PRECIOUS: mirror/eco-download.owl\n515: \n516: mirror/cob-download.owl: $(SRC)\n517: \twget --no-check-certificate $(COB_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n518: .PRECIOUS: mirror/cob-download.owl\n519: \n520: mirror/ro-download.owl: $(SRC)\n521: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/ro.owl $(WGET_OUT)\n522: .PRECIOUS: mirror/ro-download.owl\n523: \n524: # general case: download remote OWL first\n525: mirror/%-download.owl: $(SRC)\n526: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/$*.owl $(WGET_OUT)\n527: .PRECIOUS: mirror/%-download.owl\n528: \n529: mirror/users.ttl:\n530: \tcurl -L -o $@.tmp 'https://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/users.ttl' &&\\\n531: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $@.tmp --ontology-iri 'http://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/users.ttl' -o $@\n532: \n533: mirror/groups.ttl:\n534: \tcurl -L -o $@.tmp 'https://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/groups.ttl' &&\\\n535: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $@.tmp --ontology-iri 'http://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/groups.ttl' -o $@\n536: \n537: ../resources/rhea.rdf.gz:\n538: \tcurl -L -o $@ 'https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/rhea/rdf/rhea.rdf.gz'\n539: \n540: ../resources/rhea.rdf: ../resources/rhea.rdf.gz\n541: \t gunzip $< -c > $@\n542: \n543: ../resources/obsolete_ec.txt:\n544: \tcurl -L -o ../resources/enzyme.rdf 'https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/enzyme/enzyme.rdf' &&\\\n545: \tarq -q --data=../resources/enzyme.rdf --query=../sparql/query-obsolete-ec.sparql --results=tsv | tail -n +2 | sort >$@\n546: \n547: # bio-chebi.owl imports chebi and injects GCI axioms to conflate conjugate bases. See Hill et al\n548: bio-chebi.owl: mirror/chebi.owl chebi-ph7_3-slim.ofn biochebi_gcis.ofn imports/substance_by_role.owl\n549: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< -i chebi-ph7_3-slim.ofn -i biochebi_gcis.ofn -i imports/substance_by_role.owl annotate --ontology-iri $(BASE)/extensions/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/extensions/$@ -o $@.tmp.owl && mv $@.tmp.owl $@\n550: \n551: ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv:\n552: \twget 'ftp://ftp.expasy.org/databases/rhea/tsv/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv' $(WGET_OUT)\n553: \n554: ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_terms.txt: ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv\n555: \ttail -n +2 $< | cut -f 2 | sort -n -u | sed 's/^/http:\\/\\/purl.obolibrary.org\\/obo\\/CHEBI_/' >$@\n556: \n557: chebi-ph7_3-slim.ofn: ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv\n558: \techo 'Ontology(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go/extensions/chebi-ph7_3-slim.ofn>' >$@.tmp &&\\\n559: \techo 'Declaration(AnnotationProperty(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#SubsetProperty>))' >>$@.tmp &&\\\n560: \techo 'Declaration(AnnotationProperty(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go#chebi_ph7_3>))' >>$@.tmp &&\\\n561: \techo 'SubAnnotationPropertyOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go#chebi_ph7_3> <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#SubsetProperty>)' >>$@.tmp &&\\\n562: \ttail -n +2 $< | cut -f 2 | sort -n -u | sed 's/^/AnnotationAssertion(<http:\\/\\/www.geneontology.org\\/formats\\/oboInOwl#inSubset> <http:\\/\\/purl.obolibrary.org\\/obo\\/CHEBI_/' | sed 's/$$/> <http:\\/\\/purl.obolibrary.org\\/obo\\/go#chebi_ph7_3>)/' >>$@.tmp\n563: \techo ')' >>$@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n564: \n565: biochebi_gcis.tsv: ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv ../biochebi/biochebi_excludes.txt\n566: \techo 'source_chem\tstandard_chem' >$@.tmp &&\\\n567: \ttail -n +2 ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv | awk -v FS='\\t' -v OFS='\\t' '{ if ($$1 != $$2) { print \"CHEBI:\"$$1, \"CHEBI:\"$$2} }' | grep -v -f ../biochebi/biochebi_excludes.txt >> $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n568: \n569: biochebi_gcis.ofn: biochebi_gcis.tsv ../biochebi/biochebi_gcis.yaml\n570: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --obo-prefixes=true --generate-defined-class=true --template=../biochebi/biochebi_gcis.yaml --infile=$< --outfile=$@.tmp.ofn && mv $@.tmp.ofn $@\n571: \n572: ../biochebi/go-lego-chebi-import-terms.txt: imports/chebi_terms_combined.txt ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_terms.txt\n573: \tcat $^ >$@\n574: \n575: imports/go-lego-chebi-import.owl: bio-chebi.owl ../biochebi/go-lego-chebi-import-terms.txt\n576: \t$(ROBOT) extract -i $< -T ../biochebi/go-lego-chebi-import-terms.txt --method BOT annotate -O $(BASE)/imports/go-lego-chebi-import.owl -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/imports/go-lego-chebi-import.owl -o $@\n577: \n578: .PRECIOUS: mirror/uberon.owl\n579: \n580: # Avoid filtering xref annotations. dbxrefs for three-letter codes are needed in Amigo.\n581: mirror/eco.owl: mirror/eco-download.owl\n582: \tcp $< $@\n583: \n584: # NCBITaxon must be special-cased due to the mixed-case prefix\n585: mirror/ncbitaxon.owl: mirror/ncbitaxon-download.owl\n586: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_' --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false remove --select imports --trim false annotate --ontology-iri $(OBO)/$@ --output $@\n587: \n588: # WBbt must be special-cased due to the mixed-case prefix\n589: # We are already downloading its base file, but there is still some duplicative RO content it it.\n590: mirror/wbbt.owl: mirror/wbbt-download.owl\n591: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/WBbt_' --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false remove --select imports --trim false annotate --ontology-iri $(OBO)/$@ --output $@\n592: \n593: mirror/ro.owl: mirror/ro-download.owl\n594: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_' --axioms internal --preserve-structure false --trim false remove --select imports --trim false annotate --ontology-iri $(OBO)/$@ --output $@\n595: \n596: mirror/cob.owl: mirror/cob-download.owl\n597: \t# retain annotations for some ontologies which we don't import\n598: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --select 'COB:* MOP:* IAO:* OBI:* BFO:* PCO:* ENVO:*' --select complement --axioms annotation --trim false annotate --ontology-iri $(OBO)/$@ --output $@\n599: \n600: mirror/%.owl: mirror/%-download.owl\n601: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/$(shell echo $* | tr '[:lower:]' '[:upper:]')_' --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false remove --select imports --trim false annotate --ontology-iri $(OBO)/$@ --output $@\n602: # remove --term 'http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref' --trim false # need newer ROBOT version to do this without dropping definitions and synonyms\n603: #remove --drop-axiom-annotations all # need newer ROBOT version\n604: .PRECIOUS: mirror/%.owl\n605: \n606: # ----------------------------------------\n607: # CHEBI ROLES\n608: # ----------------------------------------\n609: \n610: HAS_ROLE = RO:0000087\n611: \n612: role.obo: mirror/chebi.owl\n613: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --term CHEBI:50906 --select \"self descendants\" --select \"complement\" --select \"classes\" annotate -O $(OBO)/go/chebi/role.owl -o $@\n614: \n615: imports/substance_by_role_equiv.obo: role.obo\n616: \t../util/make-substance-by-role.pl -s 'role' -r $(HAS_ROLE) $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n617: \n618: imports/substance_by_role.owl: imports/substance_by_role_equiv.obo\n619: \t$(ROBOT) reason -i $< --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural remove --axioms equivalent -o $@\n620: \n621: imports/substance_by_role.obo: imports/substance_by_role.owl\n622: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n623: \n624: # ----------------------------------------\n625: # IMPORTED AND TRANSFERRED RHEA AXIOMS\n626: # ----------------------------------------\n627: \n628: rhea.ttl: ../sparql/construct-rhea-reactions.sparql ../resources/rhea.rdf\n629: \tarq -q --data=../resources/rhea.rdf --query=../sparql/construct-rhea-reactions.sparql --results=turtle >$@\n630: \n631: extensions/rhea-reactions.ttl: rhea.ttl\n632: \t$(AMM) ../util/construct_rhea_ontology.sc $< rhea-reactions.ofn && \\\n633: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i rhea-reactions.ofn -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n634: \n635: extensions/rhea-reactions-simple.ttl: rhea.ttl\n636: \t$(AMM) ../util/construct_rhea_ontology_simplified.sc $< rhea-reactions-simple.ofn && \\\n637: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i rhea-reactions-simple.ofn -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n638: \n639: imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl: extensions/rhea-reactions-simple.ttl $(SRC)\n640: \t$(AMM) ../util/transfer_rhea_relations.sc $< $(SRC) catalog-v001.xml $@.tmp && \\\n641: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $@.tmp -O $(BASE)/$@ -o $@\n642: \n643: imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.obo: imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl\n644: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n645: \n646: # ----------------------------------------\n647: # MAPPINGS\n648: # ----------------------------------------\n649: EXTERNAL2GO_DBS = EC KEGG_REACTION MetaCyc Reactome RESID UM-BBD_enzymeID UM-BBD_pathwayID UM-BBD_reactionID Wikipedia RHEA\n650: \n651: # See : https://github.com/geneontology/go-site/issues/688\n652: # Manually add all ID spaces here; only do this for xrefs that are managed within the obo file.\n653: .PHONY: generate-mappings\n654: generate-mappings: $(ONT)-pre.ofn\n655: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --external-mappings-files -o external2go --label-prefix GO: --externals $(EXTERNAL2GO_DBS)\n656: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/interpro2go -O external2go/interpro2go\n657: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/pfam2go -O external2go/pfam2go\n658: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/pirsf2go -O external2go/pirsf2go\n659: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/prints2go -O external2go/prints2go\n660: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/prosite2go -O external2go/prosite2go\n661: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/smart2go -O external2go/smart2go\n662: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/uniprotkb_kw2go -O external2go/uniprotkb_kw2go\n663: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/uniprotkb_sl2go -O external2go/uniprotkb_sl2go\n664: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/unirule2go -O external2go/unirule2go\n665: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/hamap2go -O external2go/hamap2go\n666: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/rfam2go -O external2go/rfam2go\n667: \n668: # ----------------------------------------\n669: # TAXON GROUPINGS\n670: # ----------------------------------------\n671: \n672: imports/go-taxon-groupings.owl: imports/go-taxon-groupings-edit.owl imports/ncbitaxon_import.owl\n673: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< -i imports/ncbitaxon_import.owl reason -r jfact --axiom-generators \"SubClass EquivalentClass DisjointClasses\" query --update ../sparql/delete-redundant-disjoints-1.ru --update ../sparql/delete-redundant-disjoints-2.ru --update ../sparql/delete-redundant-disjoints-3.ru --update ../sparql/add-taxon-disjoints.ru --update ../sparql/add-in-taxon-disjoints.ru unmerge -i imports/ncbitaxon_import.owl -o $@\n674: \n675: imports/go-taxon-groupings.obo: imports/go-taxon-groupings.owl\n676: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@.tmp.obo && grep -v ^owl-axioms $@.tmp.obo > $@\n677: \n678: # ----------------------------------------\n679: # VALIDATION\n680: # ----------------------------------------\n681: \n682: # these live in the ../sparql directory, and have suffix -violation.sparql\n683: # adding the name here will make the violation check live\n684: \n685: VCHECKS = equivalent-classes trailing-whitespace owldef-self-reference synonym-label-match replacedby-obsolete replacedby-namespace missing-namespace duplicate-exact-synonym duplicate-synonym non-IRI-value non-anyURI-value obsolete-definition definition-constraints one-to-one-xrefs-by-subject one-to-one-xrefs-by-value xref-syntax\n686: \n687: # run all violation checks\n688: VARGS = $(foreach V,$(VCHECKS), $(SPARQLDIR)/$V-violation.sparql)\n689: sparql_test: go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn reasoned.ofn\n690: \t$(ROBOT) verify --input $< --queries $(VARGS) -O reports/\n691: \t# These purposely aren't checking problems in imports\n692: \t$(ROBOT) verify --input reasoned.ofn --queries $(SPARQLDIR)/multiple-class-links-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/obsolete-reference-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/missing_superclass-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/different-namespace-violation.sparql -O reports/\n693: \n694: # use this to run tests on an individual basis\n695: reports/%-violation.csv: $(SRC)\n696: \t$(ROBOT) query -i $< -s $(SPARQLDIR)/$*-violation.sparql $@\n697: \n698: check-obsolete-references-including-imports: reasoned.ofn\n699: \t$(ROBOT) merge --input reasoned.ofn verify --queries $(SPARQLDIR)/obsolete-reference-violation.sparql -O reports/\n700: \n701: ## Datalog validations\n702: go-edit.facts: $(SRC)\n703: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(SRC) -o go-edit.facts.ttl &&\\\n704: \triot -q --nocheck --output ntriples go-edit.facts.ttl | sed 's/ /\\t/' | sed 's/ /\\t/' | sed 's/ \\.$$//' >$@\n705: \n706: ../resources/rhea-relationships.tsv:\n707: \twget 'https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/rhea/tsv/rhea-relationships.tsv' -O - | tail -n +2 >$@\n708: \n709: datalog-violations.tsv: go-edit.facts ../resources/obsolete_ec.txt\n710: \tsouffle ../util/ontology-qc.dl &&\\\n711: \t( [ -s $@ ] && { cat $@; exit 1; } || true ) # exit with an error if the output is not empty\n712: \n713: reports/neo-violations.report: $(GO_LEGO).owl\n714: \t$(ROBOT) report --input $(GO_LEGO).owl --tdb true --tdb-directory tdb/ -k true -p ../sparql/neo/profile.txt -o $@ --print 50 -v\n715: \n716: # intermediate files in this target must be lexically, not numerically sorted, for use with comm\n717: # terms listed in ../biochebi/chebi-allow.txt are exempted from the pH 7.3 requirement\n718: chebi_pH_7_3_check: reports/referenced_chebi_terms.tsv ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv ../biochebi/chebi-allow.txt\n719: \ttail -n +2 reports/referenced_chebi_terms.tsv | sed 's/<http:\\/\\/purl.obolibrary.org\\/obo\\/CHEBI_//g' | sed 's/>//g' | sort -u >tmp_referenced_chebi_nums.txt &&\\\n720: \ttail -n +2 ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv | cut -f 1 | sort -u >tmp_mapped_chebi_nums.txt &&\\\n721: \ttail -n +2 ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv | cut -f 2 | sort -u >tmp_7_3_chebi_nums.txt &&\\\n722: \tgrep '^CHEBI:' ../biochebi/chebi-allow.txt | sed 's/^CHEBI://' | sort -u >tmp_chebi_allow_nums.txt &&\\\n723: \tcomm -23 tmp_referenced_chebi_nums.txt tmp_7_3_chebi_nums.txt >tmp_referenced_chebi_nums_not_7_3.txt &&\\\n724: \tcomm -23 tmp_referenced_chebi_nums_not_7_3.txt tmp_chebi_allow_nums.txt >tmp_referenced_chebi_nums_not_7_3_not_allowed.txt &&\\\n725: \tif [ -s 'tmp_referenced_chebi_nums_not_7_3_not_allowed.txt' ]; then echo \"ERROR: CHEBI IDs should be mapped to pH 7.3 (or added to ../biochebi/chebi-allow.txt):\" && cat tmp_referenced_chebi_nums_not_7_3_not_allowed.txt && exit 1; else exit 0; fi\n726: \n727: # ----------------------------------------\n728: # REPORTS\n729: # ----------------------------------------\n730: # We use `robot query` to generate TSVs from SPARQL\n731: \n732: REPORTS = owl-stats basic-report class-count-by-prefix edges labels xrefs obsoletes synonyms\n733: REPORT_ARGS = $(foreach V,$(REPORTS),-s $(SPARQLDIR)/$V.sparql reports/$V.tsv)\n734: all_reports: go.owl\n735: \t$(ROBOT) query -f tsv -i $< $(REPORT_ARGS)\n736: \n737: #all_src_reports: $(patsubst %,reports/src-%.tsv,$(REPORTS))\n738: \n739: reports/%.tsv: go.owl $(SPARQLDIR)/%.sparql $(REPORTDIR)\n740: \t$(ROBOT) -vv query -f tsv -i $< -s $(SPARQLDIR)/$*.sparql $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n741: reports/src-%.tsv: go-edit.obo $(SPARQLDIR)/%.sparql $(REPORTDIR)\n742: \t$(ROBOT) query -f tsv -i $< -s $(SPARQLDIR)/$*.sparql $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n743: \n744: reports/referenced_chebi_terms.tsv: $(SRC)\n745: \t$(ROBOT) query -f tsv -i $< --query $(SPARQLDIR)/referenced-chebi-terms.sparql $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n746: \n747: # ----------------------------------------\n748: # DESIGN PATTERNS\n749: # ----------------------------------------\n750: \n751: ALL_PATTERN_YAMLS=$(wildcard ../design_patterns/*.yaml)\n752: ALL_PATTERN_NAMES=$(patsubst ../design_patterns/%.yaml,%,$(ALL_PATTERN_YAMLS))\n753: ALL_PATTERN_TSVS=$(patsubst %.yaml,%.tsv,$(ALL_PATTERN_YAMLS))\n754: \n755: # Currently not rebuilt automatically; waiting for updated dosdp-tools in ODK\n756: imports/go-pattern-conformance.ttl: reasoned.ofn $(ALL_PATTERN_YAMLS)\n757: \trm -f ../design_patterns/*.tsv &&\\\n758: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) query --obo-prefixes=true --batch-patterns=\"$(ALL_PATTERN_NAMES)\" --template=../design_patterns --outfile=../design_patterns --ontology=reasoned.ofn --catalog=catalog-v001.xml --reasoner=elk --parallelism=4 --output-conformance=$@.tmp &&\\\n759: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $@.tmp --ontology-iri $(BASE)/$@ -o $@\n760: \n761: pattern-docs: imports/go-pattern-conformance.ttl reasoned.ofn $(ALL_PATTERN_YAMLS) $(ALL_PATTERN_TSVS)\n762: \trm -f ../../docs/patterns/*.md &&\\\n763: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) docs --obo-prefixes=true --batch-patterns=\"$(ALL_PATTERN_NAMES)\" --template=../design_patterns --outfile=../../docs/patterns --infile=../design_patterns --data-location-prefix='https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/tree/master/src/design_patterns/' --ontology=reasoned.ofn --catalog=catalog-v001.xml\n\n(End of file - total 763 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"all: stage_release\n\nSHELL=./stamp.sh\n\n# ----------------------------------------\n# CORE VARIABLES\n# ----------------------------------------\n\n# base URI for all OBO library ontologies\nOBO=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo\n\n# OBO name of this ontology (always lowercase)\nONT=go\n\n# Base URL for ontology\nBASE=$(OBO)/$(ONT)\n\n# Source file edited by editors\nSRC=$(ONT)-edit.obo\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"src/ontology/Makefile","time":{"start":1778467380252,"end":1778467380260}},"id":"prt_e14ea950f001R4eGyljF58UWdE","sessionID":"ses_1eb261946ffeivpfqyEeGx6tvF","messageID":"msg_e14ea84ab0015wDM5WlQ1X2w49"}}
