ty_value: http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title \"Gene Ontology\" xsd:string\n55: property_value: http://purl.org/dc/terms/license http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\n56: \n57: [Term]\n58: id: GO:0000001\n59: name: mitochondrion inheritance\n60: namespace: biological_process\n61: def: \"The distribution of mitochondria, including the mitochondrial genome, into daughter cells after mitosis or meiosis, mediated by interactions between mitochondria and the cytoskeleton.\" [GOC:mcc, PMID:10873824, PMID:11389764]\n62: synonym: \"mitochondrial inheritance\" EXACT []\n63: is_a: GO:0048311 ! mitochondrion distribution\n64: intersection_of: GO:0048308 ! organelle inheritance\n65: intersection_of: results_in_distribution_of GO:0005739 ! mitochondrion\n66: \n67: [Term]\n68: id: GO:0000002\n69: name: obsolete mitochondrial genome maintenance\n70: namespace: biological_process\n71: def: \"OBSOLETE. The maintenance of the structure and integrity of the mitochondrial genome; includes replication and segregation of the mitochondrial chromosome.\" [GOC:ai, GOC:vw]\n72: comment: This term described phenotypic observations for multiple processes (including transport/lipid metabolism/ DNA metabolism/ fission/ fusion etc)\n73: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29646\" xsd:anyURI\n74: is_obsolete: true\n75: \n76: [Term]\n77: id: GO:0000003\n78: name: obsolete reproduction\n79: namespace: biological_process\n80: def: \"OBSOLETE. The production of new individuals that contain some portion of genetic material inherited from one or more parent organisms.\" [GOC:curators, GOC:isa_complete, GOC:jl, ISBN:0198506732]\n81: comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is equivalent to reproductive process.\n82: synonym: \"reproductive physiological process\" EXACT []\n83: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27054\" xsd:anyURI\n84: is_obsolete: true\n85: replaced_by: GO:0022414\n86: \n87: [Term]\n88: id: GO:0000005\n89: name: obsolete ribosomal chaperone activity\n90: namespace: molecular_function\n91: def: \"OBSOLETE. Assists in the correct assembly of ribosomes or ribosomal subunits in vivo, but is not a component of the assembled ribosome when performing its normal biological function.\" [GOC:jl, PMID:12150913]\n92: comment: This term was made obsolete because it refers to a class of gene products and a biological process rather than a molecular function.\n93: synonym: \"ribosomal chaperone activity\" EXACT []\n94: is_obsolete: true\n95: consider: GO:0042254\n96: consider: GO:0044183\n97: consider: GO:0140309\n98: \n99: [Term]\n100: id: GO:0000006\n101: name: high-affinity zinc transmembrane transporter activity\n102: namespace: molecular_function\n103: def: \"Enables the transfer of zinc ions (Zn2+) from one side of a membrane to the other, probably powered by proton motive force. In high-affinity transport the transporter is able to bind the solute even if it is only present at very low concentrations.\" [TC:2.A.5.1.1]\n104: synonym: \"high affinity zinc uptake transmembrane transporter activity\" EXACT []\n105: synonym: \"high-affinity zinc uptake transmembrane transporter activity\" RELATED []\n106: is_a: GO:0005385 ! zinc ion transmembrane transporter activity\n107: \n108: [Term]\n109: id: GO:0000007\n110: name: low-affinity zinc ion transmembrane transporter activity\n111: namespace: molecular_function\n112: def: \"Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: Zn2+ = Zn2+, probably powered by proton motive force. In low-affinity transport the transporter is able to bind the solute only if it is present at very high concentrations.\" [GOC:mtg_transport, ISBN:0815340729]\n113: is_a: GO:0005385 ! zinc ion transmembrane transporter activity\n114: \n115: [Term]\n116: id: GO:0000008\n117: name: obsolete thioredoxin\n118: namespace: molecular_function\n119: alt_id: GO:0000013\n120: def: \"OBSOLETE. A small disulfide-containing redox protein that serves as a general protein disulfide oxidoreductase. Interacts with a broad range of proteins by a redox mechanism, based on the reversible oxidation of 2 cysteine thiol groups to a disulfide, accompanied by the transfer of 2 electrons and 2 protons. The net result is the covalent interconversion of a disulfide and a dithiol.\" [GOC:kd]\n121: comment: This term was made obsolete because it represents gene products.\n122: synonym: \"thioredoxin\" EXACT []\n123: is_obsolete: true\n124: consider: GO:0003756\n125: consider: GO:0015036\n126: \n127: [Term]\n128: id: GO:0000009\n129: name: alpha-1,6-mannosyltransferase activity\n130: namespace: molecular_function\n131: def: \"Catalysis of the transfer of a mannose residue to an oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1->6) linkage.\" [GOC:mcc, PMID:2644248]\n132: synonym: \"1,6-alpha-mannosyltransferase activity\" EXACT []\n133: is_a: GO:0000030 ! mannosyltransferase activity\n134: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/19075\" xsd:anyURI\n135: \n136: [Term]\n137: id: GO:0000010\n138: name: heptaprenyl diphosphate synthase activity\n139: namespace: molecular_function\n140: alt_id: GO:0036422\n141: def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate + 4 isopentenyl diphosphate = 4 diphosphate + all-trans-heptaprenyl diphosphate.\" [PMID:9708911, RHEA:27794]\n142: synonym: \"all-trans-heptaprenyl-diphosphate synthase activity\" EXACT [EC:2.5.1.30]\n143: synonym: \"HepPP synthase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.5.1.30]\n144: synonym: \"heptaprenyl pyrophosphate synthase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.5.1.30]\n145: synonym: \"heptaprenyl pyrophosphate synthetase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.5.1.30]\n146: synonym: \"trans-hexaprenyltranstransferase activity\" EXACT []\n147: xref: EC:2.5.1.30 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\n148: xref: MetaCyc:TRANS-HEXAPRENYLTRANSTRANSFERASE-RXN\n149: xref: RHEA:27794 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\n150: is_a: GO:0120531 ! prenyl diphosphate synthase activity\n151: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/20661\" xsd:anyURI\n152: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/23472\" xsd:anyURI\n153: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27609\" xsd:anyURI\n154: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n155: created_by: bf\n156: creation_date: 2013-09-16T11:50:41Z\n157: \n158: [Term]\n159: id: GO:0000011\n160: name: vacuole inheritance\n161: namespace: biological_process\n162: def: \"The distribution of vacuoles into daughter cells after mitosis or meiosis, mediated by interactions between vacuoles and the cytoskeleton.\" [GOC:mcc, PMID:10873824, PMID:14616069]\n163: is_a: GO:0007033 ! vacuole organization\n164: intersection_of: GO:0048308 ! organelle inheritance\n165: intersection_of: results_in_distribution_of GO:0005773 ! vacuole\n166: \n167: [Term]\n168: id: GO:0000012\n169: name: single strand break repair\n170: namespace: biological_process\n171: def: \"The repair of single strand breaks in DNA. Repair of such breaks is mediated by the same enzyme systems as are used in base excision repair.\" [PMID:18626472]\n172: is_a: GO:0006281 ! DNA repair\n173: \n174: [Term]\n175: id: GO:0000014\n176: name: single-stranded DNA endonuclease activity\n177: namespace: molecular_function\n178: def: \"Catalysis of the hydrolysis of ester linkages within a single-stranded deoxyribonucleic acid molecule by creating internal breaks.\" [GOC:mah]\n179: synonym: \"single-stranded DNA endodeoxyribonuclease activity\" EXACT []\n180: synonym: \"single-stranded DNA specific endodeoxyribonuclease activity\" RELATED []\n181: synonym: \"ssDNA-specific endodeoxyribonuclease activity\" RELATED [GOC:mah]\n182: is_a: GO:0004520 ! DNA endonuclease activity\n183: is_a: GO:0016788 ! 