y more accurate terms to represent the biological processes occurring, and it is not clear that this term represents a useful entity.\n674: synonym: \"DNA replication and chromosome cycle\" EXACT []\n675: is_obsolete: true\n676: consider: GO:0006260\n677: consider: GO:0007059\n678: consider: GO:0051276\n679: \n680: [Term]\n681: id: GO:0000070\n682: name: mitotic sister chromatid segregation\n683: namespace: biological_process\n684: alt_id: GO:0016359\n685: def: \"The cell cycle process in which replicated homologous chromosomes are organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two sets during the mitotic cell cycle. Each replicated chromosome, composed of two sister chromatids, aligns at the cell equator, paired with its homologous partner. One homolog of each morphologic type goes into each of the resulting chromosome sets.\" [GOC:ai, GOC:jl]\n686: subset: goslim_pombe\n687: synonym: \"mitotic chromosome segregation\" EXACT []\n688: synonym: \"mitotic sister-chromatid adhesion release\" NARROW []\n689: is_a: GO:0000819 ! sister chromatid segregation\n690: intersection_of: GO:0098813 ! nuclear chromosome segregation\n691: intersection_of: part_of GO:0140014 ! mitotic nuclear division\n692: \n693: [Term]\n694: id: GO:0000072\n695: name: obsolete M phase specific microtubule process\n696: namespace: biological_process\n697: def: \"OBSOLETE. A microtubule-based process that occurs only during M phase of the cell cycle.\" [GOC:mah]\n698: comment: This term was made obsolete because terms already exist for centrosome/spindle organization which would be more suitable for the existing annotations, and the phase could be captured as an annotation extension if necessary.\n699: synonym: \"M phase specific microtubule process\" EXACT []\n700: synonym: \"M-phase specific microtubule process\" EXACT []\n701: is_obsolete: true\n702: consider: GO:0007017\n703: \n704: [Term]\n705: id: GO:0000073\n706: name: initial mitotic spindle pole body separation\n707: namespace: biological_process\n708: alt_id: GO:0030475\n709: def: \"The release of duplicated mitotic spindle pole bodies (SPBs) that begins with the nucleation of microtubules from each SPB within the nucleus, leading to V-shaped spindle microtubules. Interpolar microtubules that elongate from each pole are interconnected, forming overlapping microtubules. Capturing and antiparallel sliding apart of microtubules promotes the initial separation of the SPB.\" [GOC:sgd_curators, GOC:vw]\n710: is_a: GO:0110100 ! spindle pole body separation\n711: relationship: part_of GO:0061804 ! mitotic spindle formation (spindle phase one)\n712: relationship: part_of GO:1905047 ! mitotic spindle pole body organization\n713: \n714: [Term]\n715: id: GO:0000075\n716: name: cell cycle checkpoint signaling\n717: namespace: biological_process\n718: alt_id: GO:0031576\n719: alt_id: GO:0071779\n720: alt_id: GO:0072395\n721: alt_id: GO:0072404\n722: alt_id: GO:0072407\n723: def: \"A signaling process that controls cell cycle progression by monitoring the integrity of specific cell cycle events. A cell cycle checkpoint begins with detection of deficiencies or defects and ends with signal transduction.\" [GOC:mtg_cell_cycle]\n724: comment: This term should not be used in direct manual annotation as it should always be possible to minimally designate mitotic or meiotic checkpoint, and usually to additionally specify the checkpoint (i.e mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint, mitotic DNA damage checkpoint etc). Note also that the effector processes are not part of the checkpoint but are positively regulated by the checkpoint signaling and should not be annotated here.\n725: subset: gocheck_do_not_annotate\n726: synonym: \"cell cycle checkpoint\" EXACT []\n727: synonym: \"G1/S checkpoint\" NARROW []\n728: synonym: \"G1/S transition checkpoint\" NARROW []\n729: synonym: \"G2/M checkpoint\" NARROW []\n730: synonym: \"G2/M transition checkpoint\" NARROW []\n731: synonym: \"signal transduction involved in cell cycle checkpoint\" EXACT []\n732: synonym: \"signal transduction involved in G2/M transition checkpoint\" EXACT []\n733: xref: Wikipedia:Cell_cycle_checkpoint\n734: intersection_of: GO:0035556 ! intracellular signal transduction\n735: intersection_of: negatively_regulates GO:0044770 ! cell cycle phase transition\n736: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/20935\" xsd:anyURI\n737: \n738: [Term]\n739: id: GO:0000076\n740: name: DNA replication checkpoint signaling\n741: namespace: biological_process\n742: alt_id: GO:0072437\n743: def: \"A signal transduction process that contributes to a DNA replication checkpoint, that prevents the initiation of nuclear division until DNA replication is complete, thereby ensuring that progeny inherit a full complement of the genome.\" [GOC:curators, GOC:rn, PMID:11728327, PMID:12537518]\n744: synonym: \"DNA replication checkpoint\" EXACT []\n745: synonym: \"signal transduction involved in DNA replication checkpoint\" EXACT []\n746: is_a: GO:0031570 ! DNA integrity checkpoint signaling\n747: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/20935\" xsd:anyURI\n748: \n749: [Term]\n750: id: GO:0000077\n751: name: DNA damage checkpoint signaling\n752: namespace: biological_process\n753: alt_id: GO:0072422\n754: def: \"A signal transduction process that contributes to a DNA damage checkpoint.\" [GOC:mah]\n755: synonym: \"DNA damage checkpoint\" EXACT []\n756: synonym: \"DNA damage response, signal transduction resulting in cell cycle arrest\" NARROW []\n757: synonym: \"signal transduction involved in DNA damage checkpoint\" EXACT []\n758: xref: Wikipedia:DNA_damage_checkpoint\n759: xref: Wikipedia:Postreplication_checkpoint\n760: is_a: GO:0006974 ! DNA damage response\n761: is_a: GO:0031570 ! DNA integrity checkpoint signaling\n762: is_a: GO:0042770 ! signal transduction in response to DNA damage\n763: created_by: mah\n764: creation_date: 2010-12-08T04:18:11Z\n765: \n766: [Term]\n767: id: GO:0000078\n768: name: obsolete cytokinesis after mitosis checkpoint\n769: namespace: biological_process\n770: def: \"OBSOLETE. A mitotic cell cycle checkpoint that detects whether chromosome segregation is complete and negatively regulates cytokinesis following mitosis.\" [GOC:mtg_cell_cycle]\n771: comment: The reason this term was made obsolete is that the two terms cytokinesis checkpoint (GO:0031565) and cytokinesis after mitosis (GO:0000078) were conflated in meaning.\n772: synonym: \"cell morphogenesis checkpoint\" EXACT [GOC:dph, GOC:vw]\n773: synonym: \"cell shape checkpoint\" EXACT []\n774: is_obsolete: true\n775: consider: GO:0044878\n776: consider: GO:0044879\n777: \n778: [Term]\n779: id: GO:0000079\n780: name: regulation of cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity\n781: namespace: biological_process\n782: def: \"Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity.\" [GOC:curators, GOC:pr]\n783: subset: gocheck_obsoletion_candidate\n784: synonym: \"regulation of CDK activity\" EXACT []\n785: synonym: \"regulation of cyclin-dependent protein kinase activity\" BROAD []\n786: intersection_of: GO:0065007 ! biological regulation\n787: intersection_of: regulates GO:0004693 ! cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity\n788: \n789: [Term]\n790: id: GO:0000080\n791: name: mitotic G1 phase\n792: namespace: biological_process\n793: def: \"The cell cycle 'gap' phase which is the interval between the completion of DNA segregation by mitosis and the beginning of DNA synthesis.\" [GOC:mtg_cell_cycle]\n794: comment: Note that this term should not be used for direct annotation. If you are trying to make an annotation to x phase, it is likely that the correct annotation is 'regulation of x/y phase transition' or to a process which occurs during the reported phase (i.e mitotic DNA replication for mitotic S-phase). To capture the phase when a specific location or process is observed, the phase term can be used in an annotation extension (PMID:24885854) applied to a cellular component term (with the relation exists_during) or a biological process term (with the relation happens_during).\n795: subset: gocheck_do_not_annotate\n796: synonym: \"G1 phase of mitotic cell cycle\" EXACT []\n797: is_a: GO:0051318 ! G1 phase\n798: relationship: part_of GO:0051329 ! mitotic interphase\n799: \n800: [Term]\n801: id: GO:0000082\n802: name: G1/S transition of mitotic cell cycle\n803: namespace: biological_process\n804: def: \"The mitotic cell cycle transition by which a cell in G1 commits to S phase. The process begins with the build up of G1 cyclin-dependent kinase (G1 CDK), resulting in the activation of transcription of G1 cyclins. The process ends with the positive feedback of the G1 cyclins on the G1 CDK which commits the cell to S phase, in which DNA replication is initiated.\" [GOC:mtg_cell_cycle]\n805: intersection_of: GO:0044843 ! cell cycle G1/S phase transition\n806: intersection_of: part_of GO:0000278 ! mitotic cell cycle\n807: \n808: [Term]\n809: id: GO:0000083\n810: name: obsolete regulation of transcription involved in G1/S transition of mitotic cell cycle\n811: namespace: biological_process\n812: def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that regulates transcription such that the target genes are involved in the transition between G1 and S phase of the mitotic cell cycle.\" [GOC:mtg_cell_cycle]\n813: comment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a GO-CAM model.\n814: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26002\" xsd:anyURI\n815: is_obsolete: true\n816: consider: GO:0000082\n817: consider: GO:0006357\n818: \n819: [Term]\n820: id: GO:0000084\n821: name: mitotic S phase\n822: namespace: biological_process\n823: def: \"The cell cycle phase, following G1, during which DNA synthesis takes place as part of a mitotic cell cycle.\" [GOC:mtg_cell_cycle]\n824: comment: Note 